{"id": "EUVD-2021-34650", "enisaUuid": "27bed123-6918-3089-b48a-6711e3bdc026", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nmedia: venus: vdec: fixed possible memory leak issue\n\nThe venus_helper_alloc_dpb_bufs() implementation allows an early return\non an error path when checking the id from ida_alloc_min() which would\nnot release the earlier buffer allocation.\n\nMove the direct kfree() from the error checking of dma_alloc_attrs() to\nthe common fail path to ensure that allocations are released on all\nerror paths in this function.\n\nAddresses-Coverity: 1494120 (\"Resource leak\")", "datePublished": "2025-02-26T01:54:19", "dateUpdated": "2025-10-01T19:57:07", "baseScore": 5.5, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:L/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:H", "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/5cedfe8aaf1875a5305897107b7f298db4260019", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/55bccafc246b2e64763a155ec454470c07a54a6e", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/5f89d05ba93df9c2cdfe493843f93288e55e99eb", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/8403fdd775858a7bf04868d43daea0acbe49ddfc", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2021-47655"], "aliases": ["CVE-2021-47655"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.04, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "037543a9-9ea6-390d-8196-6f7dba376460", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "40d87aafee29fb01ce1e1868502fb2059a6a7f34 <8403fdd775858a7bf04868d43daea0acbe49ddfc"}, {"id": "12a3f529-d04c-3477-adf1-33fe853524ca", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.17.2"}, {"id": "12edc6e0-5e9c-3200-852c-f34c01e4777f", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.18"}, {"id": "3d14ca7e-31f7-3117-8237-2e3bddaffdf3", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "5.16"}, {"id": "51a12202-fed9-3788-af33-109fa151d2a2", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "40d87aafee29fb01ce1e1868502fb2059a6a7f34 <55bccafc246b2e64763a155ec454470c07a54a6e"}, {"id": "67474122-60